        eventYear: 1909,
        country: null,
        localityVerbatim: "Plate 10 from  Seitz,1912- 1913  A. Ed. Die Großschmetterlinge der Erde, Verlag Alfred Kernen, Stuttgart  Band 2: Abt. 1, Die Großschmetterlinge des palaearktischen Faunengebietes, Die palaearktischen Spinner und Schwärmer, 1912- 1913 The Macrolepidoptera of the world : a systematic account of all the known Macrolepidoptera Volume 2 (1912-1916) text online read text See The Global Lepidoptera Names Index for valid names\n\n10a\nEpicopeia hainesii Holland, 1889\nEpicopeia sinicaria Leech ?\nEpicopeia mencia Moore, [1875]\n\n10b\nEpicopeia excisa Butler ?\nEpicopeia caroli Janet ?\n\n10c\nNola cucullatella (Linnaeus, 1758)\nAntennola impura (Mann, 1862) (syn.: Nola impura)\nNola phaea Hampson, 1900\nMeganola togatulalis (Hübner, 1796) (syn.: Roeselia togatulalis)\nMeganola albula (Denis &amp; Schiffermüller, 1775) (syn.: Roeselia albula)\n\n10d\nMeganola scripta (Moore, 1888) (syn.: Roeselia scripta)\nMeganola gigantula (Staudinger, 1879) (syn.: Roeselia gigantula)\nMeganola maculata (Staudinger in Romanoff, 1887)Roeselia maculata)\nMeganola nitida (Hampson, 1894) (syn.: Roeselia nitida)\nMeganola fumosa (Butler, 1879) (syn.: Roeselia fumosa)\nMeganola bryophilalis (Staudinger, 1887) (syn.: Roeselia bryophilalis)\nMeganola triangulalis (Leech, 1888) (syn.:Roeselia triangulalis)\nNola karelica tigranula Püngeler, 1902 (syn.: Roeselia tigranula)\n\n10e\nMeganola costalis (Staudinger, 1887) (syn.: Roeselia costalis)\nNola acutula Püngeler, 1902 (syn.: Roeselia acutula)\nMeganola strigula (Denis &amp; Schiffermüller, 1775) (syn.: Roeselia strigula)\nEvonima mandschuriana (Oberthür, 1880) (syn.: Mimerastria mandschuriana)\nMeganola longiventris (Poujade, 1886) Mimerastria longiventris)\nNola cicatricalis (Treitschke, 1835) (syn.: Celama cicatricalis)\nNola ancipitalis (Herrich-Schäffer, [1851]) (syn.: Celama ancipitalis)\n\n10f\nNola confusalis (Herrich-Schäffer, [1851]) (syn.: Celama confusalis)\nNola aerugula (Hübner, 1793) (syn.: Celema centonalis)\nNola aerugula (Hübner, 1793) (syn.: Glaphyra atomosa Bremer, 1861)\nNola cristatula (Hübner, 1793) (syn.: Celema cristatula)\nNola chlamitulalis (Hübner, [1813]) (syn.: Celema chlamitulalis)\n\n10g\nNola chlamitulalis (Hübner, [1813]) (forma minutalis Leech)\nNola taeniata Snellen, 1875 (syn.: Celema candida)\nNola angulata (Moore, 1888) (syn.: Celema angulata)\nNola squalida Staudinger, 1870 (syn.: Celema squalida)\nNola innocua Butler, 1880 (syn.: Celema innocua)\nNola flexuosa Poujade, 1886 (syn.: Celema flexuosa)\nNola aegyptiaca Snellen, 1875 (syn.: Celema aegyptiaca)\n\nNola thymula Millière, 1868 (syn.: Celema thymula)",
