        localityVerbatim: "Rhopalocera nihonica: a description of the butterflies of Japan. By H. Pryer. Plate 10\nPlate Text\nPlate 10\n\n1 Pronophila schrenkii Men = Ninguta schrenckii (Ménétriés, 1859)\n2 Neope calipteris Butler= Lethe callipteris (Butler, 1877)\n3 Coenonympha  oedipus  Fab.= Coenonympha oedippus (Fabricius, 1787)\n4 Ismene benjamani= Guer. =  Ismene benjamini; Moore, 1878= Hesperia benjaminii Guérin-Méneville, 1843 = Choaspes benjaminii (Guérin-Méneville, 1843\n5A Pythauria  chrysaeglia  But. =  Bibasis aquilina chrysaeglia (Butler, [1882])\n5B Pythauria  chrysoeglia  But.\n6 Daimio tethys  Murray = Daimio tethys (MÉNÉTRIÉS, 1857).\n7 Pamphila mathias  Fab. =Pelopidas mathias (Fabricius, 1798)\n8 Pamphila lamprospilus Feld =Isoteinon lamprospilus C. &amp; R. Felder, 1862\n9 Pamphila varia Murray = Thoressa varia (Murray, 1875)\n10 Pamphila guttata Brem.  = Eudamus guttatus Bremer &amp; Grey, [1852] = Parnara guttatus (Bremer &amp; Grey, [1852])\n11 Pamphila pellucida Murray= Polytremis pellucida (Murray, 1875)\n12 Pamphila jansonis But. =Pelopidas jansonis (Butler, 1878)\n13A Hesperia sylvanus Esp. = Ochlodes sylvanus (Esper, 1777)\n13B Hesperia sylvanus Esp.\n14A Hesperia comma Linn. = Hesperia comma (Linnaeus, 1758)\n14B Hesperia comma Linn.\n15 Hesperia leonine But. = Thymelicus leonina (Butler, 1878)\n16A Hesperia rikuchina But. rikuchina Butler, 1878 =Ochlodes ochracea (Bremer, 1861)\n16B Hesperia rikuchina But.\n17 Hesperia flava Murray =  Potanthus flava (Murray, 1875)\n18 Hesperia sp.\n19 Cyclopides ornatus Brem. = Leptalina unicolor (Bremer &amp; Grey, [1852])\n20 Pyrgus inachus  Men.= Aeromachus inachus (Ménétriés, 1859)\n21 Syrichthus maculatus Bremer and Grey = Pyrgus maculatus (Bremer &amp; Grey, 1853)\n22 Syrichthus sinicus =  Pyrgus sinicus Butler, 1877= = Pyrgus maculatus (Bremer &amp; Grey, 1853)\n23 Nisoniades montanus Brem. = Erynnis montanus (Bremer, 1861)\n24 Melanitis n.sp",
